Input: n = 7, k = 3
Output: 4
Explanation: The elimination order is 3 → 6 → 2 → 7 → 5 → 1, and the person at position 4 survives.
================
class Solution {
    public int josephus(int n, int k) {
        // code here
        if(n == 1) return 1;
        return (josephus(n-1, k) + k - 1) % n + 1;
    }
}
